OL,7,FSpain, Portugal and Morocco are set
OL,8,Fto co-host the 2030 men's World Cup,
OL,9,Fwith three South American nations
OL,10,Fstaging the opening matches to mark
OL,11,Fthe tournament's centenary.
OL,13,FMontevideo in Uruguay, the city which
OL,14,Fhosted the first World Cup finals
OL,15,Fmatch in 1930, is poised to stage the
OL,16,Fopening match in seven years' time,
OL,17,Fwith games in Argentina and Paraguay
OL,18,Fto follow.
